# IPTV Tuner Module Structure

```
modules/iptv_tuner/
  manifest.json              # id: com.240mp.iptv_tuner
  assets/images/logo.svg
  views/
    Root.qml                 # router (required)
    Channels.qml             # channel list / tuner
    Guide.qml                # TV Guide / Prevue-style EPG
    Player.qml               # mpv hand-off for live streams
    Weather.qml              # future — Weather Channel screen

src/modules/iptv_tuner/
  IptvTunerBackend.h/.cpp    # M3U/XMLTV fetch, parse, cache, signals to QML
```

## manifest.json (planned settings)

| key | type | purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `enabled` | toggle | Module on/off |
| `m3u_url` | text* | M3U playlist URL or file path |
| `epg_url` | text* | XMLTV URL override (optional if M3U header has `url-tvg`) |
| `guide_mode` | list_single | `passive` / `interactive` |
| `guide_theme` | list_single | Guide visual theme |
| `auto_zoom_widescreen` | toggle | mpv auto-zoom 16:9 content |
| `refresh_guide` | action | Re-fetch M3U + EPG |

\*Requires `text` setting type in shell, or use `directory_browser` for local files until added.

## C++ backend (`IptvTunerBackend`)

Follow `PlexBackend` conventions:

- `QObject` subclass; `Q_INVOKABLE` slots for QML; `signals:` for async results.
- HTTP via `QNetworkAccessManager` on the main thread.
- Optional `onSettingChanged(QString, QString, QVariant)` for settings reactions.
- Emit parsed data as `QVariantList` of `QVariantMap` objects QML can bind to.

Suggested signals:

```cpp
void channelsLoaded(const QVariant &channels);
void guideDataReady(const QVariant &channels, const QVariant &programmes);
void loadFailed(const QString &message);
void dynamicOptionsReady(const QString &key, const QVariant &options); // if needed
```

Suggested invokables: `loadChannels()`, `loadGuide()`, `getChannelStreamUrl(QString tvgId)`.

## Live playback (`Player.qml`)

Hand off to mpv — pattern from `modules/local_files/views/Player.qml` and `ambient_mode/views/Player.qml`:

- Live `.ts` streams: `mpvController.loadAndPlay(streamUrl, 0.0, 0, -1)` — no resume offset.
- Forward remote keys to mpv via `mpvController.sendKey()` while playing.
- On `playbackFinished` / user exit → `goBack()` to channel list or guide.
- Channel change: stop current mpv session, load new URL (analog transition UI wraps this in QML).
- **Auto-zoom:** extend `MpvController::loadAndPlay` or pass mpv flags for widescreen (e.g. `--video-zoom`, `--panscan`) when `auto_zoom_widescreen` is ON — keep logic in one place.

## QML navigation

Follow `ARCHITECTURE.md` exactly:

- `Root.qml`: `id: moduleRoot`, `navigateTo` / `navigateBack`, `goBack()` exits module.
- Views: `FocusScope`, `property var navParams`, signals not direct router calls.
- Pass channel objects via `navParams` to `Player.qml` and `Guide.qml`.

## CMake / main.cpp checklist

1. Add `src/modules/iptv_tuner/IptvTunerBackend.cpp` to `CMakeLists.txt`.
2. `#include` + construct in `main.cpp`.
3. `registerModule("com.240mp.iptv_tuner", "iptvTunerBackend", …)`.
